U.S.: Repetition is the mother of wisdom
It is funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the foolishest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, expected anxiously, it was shown that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only in the same text is the words "equal as in Iraq" used several times, but it also also hesitated to use the title of Bush's January 2007 declaration for his own statement: "A new way forward".
He was himself, who criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from civil war three years ago, and that was criticized as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences".
The following months, however, showed that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful one, so that nothing is spoken of in the news today.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however objectively left his successor a situation far more favourable than it might have been expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will be repeated.
The country captains once again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan operation General Stanley McCristal. He, even in spite of the traditional subordinate relations, subjected the undecided gunmen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He requested 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president wavered for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he tricked the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he himself previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic of Obama's whole strategy seems to be its goal, to start withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and finalizing this procedure in three years. Obama's whole doctrine generated more questions than the answers it offered.
Many doubt that the increase yields the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq’s society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing their boss every day according to their needs.
The political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. The patriarchal tribal relations will remain behind him.
Balance the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confused relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even to establish a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the whole operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy shocks for its volunteerism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to the war to "go home soon," will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date of withdrawal of troops is a purely irresponsible one, since the Taliban will regard it as an indirect declaration of U.S. defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that Europeans are increasingly reluctant to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions do not have any effect on the Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: to try to solve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to look for the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America starts the triumphal withdrawal of troops from Afghanistan.
However, each solution will mean a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if this is a total failure.
