Internet auction of crashed cars
Last October, the Solera group bought Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars such as motorcycles or damaged special vehicles.
The operation involved a disbursement of EUR 59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could be extended to the remaining 15% in the year.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing a huge international market.
This valuation and sale service is aimed exclusively at industry professionals, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, workshops, scrapers and professional sellers who must register before starting operations.
This platform was set up in Germany in 1996 and runs over 650,000 operations across Europe, 500,000 of which in Germany.
Its main markets include Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
The website currently has more than 1,500 registered sellers and 4,000 experts.
3,000 daily ads are managed and some 100 new ads are included in the Spanish market every day.
