Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audatex company guarantees that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, looking for the replacement, creating the budget and generating the budget.
The ease of use is an essential condition for these systems, especially to convince older professionals, who are, to a greater or lesser extent, more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 tourism, 109 allterrestrials, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, a computer with Internet connection is needed to use it.
Once the model has been identified to be repaired by its frame number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user may include variables such as the price of the workforce, charges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a valuation tool like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the one oriented to the workshop does not include estimated working time.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is EUR 350 per year, which the customer can finance.
Currently the Audatex company is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with very good eyes, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inside face.
